#!/usr/local/projects/routing/help/html_filter.pl
<h2 align=center>Help for the "Distributor" search menu</h2>
You usually reach this menu by clicking on the 'Distributors' button
at the footer of this application.
<p>The Distributor search menu allows you to search through all the
distributors you have access to (usually only one), and select
which one to operate in.
<p>
The header for the search table shows the description of each of the columns.
If you click on the column header, you can enter a value and only show
distributors with the specified value in that field.

In practice this is useless with only one distributor.
<p>
Values in the search output are clickable:
<ul>
<li>Clicking on a <a href="record_Distributor.cgi">distributor</a> name will view information about
    that distributor.
<li>Clicking the <a href="field_Distributor_Address.cgi">address</a> will bring up Google map directions to get there.
<li>Clicking the <a href="field_Distributor_Phone.cgi">phone number</a> will bring up your phone
    application (if available).
<li>Clicking on a <a href="record_Staff.cgi">contact</a> name will bring up the record associated
    with that staff member associated with that distributor.
</ul>

